Governor David Umahi of Ebonyi State has confirmed the first index case of coronavirus pandemic in the state. In a statewide broadcast yesterday evening, Umahi said that the patient is a 31 year-old man from Ukawu in Onicha local government area. The patient, who is a commercial driver, according to the governor, usually carries food items from the South East to Ondo State and after selling them, conveys passengers back to his base in the state. He explained that he had this year made two journeys, one on 29th March and returned to Ebonyi on 1st April and on 12th April. The governor said that on the patient’s last visit to Ore in Ondo State, he was unable to get passengers to the East which prompted him to sleep at motor parks and filling stations in the area. Governor Umahi noted that he later made his way back to the state through Ishiagu in Ivo local government area to Afikpo North LGA and down to Okposi in Ohaozara local government area of the state before he was apprehended by the council chairman who handed him over to the police and members of the state security outfit. Governor Umahi said that as part of the state government’s policy the suspect along with others was to the Abakaliki Township Stadium for quarantining and testing. He said that when the suspects were tested twice, only the commercial driver was confirmed positive. Umahi said that the others numbering over 300 who illegally entered the state through the boundaries and were arrested and quarantined tested negative.